choices.text:
{
  "Ingredients": [
    "Fish Fillets",
    "Flour",
    "Salt",
    "Egg",
    "Breadcrumbs",
    "Oil",
    "Potatoes"
  ],
  "Instructions": [
    "1. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).",
    "2. Rinse the fish fillets and pat dry with paper towels.",
    "3. In a shallow bowl, mix together the flour, salt, and pepper.",
    "4. In a separate shallow bowl, beat the egg. In a third shallow bowl, mix together the breadcrumbs.",
    "5. Dip the fish fillets in the flour mixture, then the egg, and then the breadcrumbs.",
    "6. Place the coated fish fillets on a greased baking sheet.",
    "7. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes, or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.",
    "8. Meanwhile, heat oil in a deep-fryer or large saucepan to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).",
    "9. Peel and cut the potatoes into thick strips.",
    "10. Fry the potatoes in the hot oil until golden brown, about 5 minutes. Drain on paper towels.",
    "11. Serve the fish and chips hot."
  ]
}
